 TWO ladies were on Sunday night raped by robbers in a hotel in Awka North local council of Anambra State. The robbers dispossessed lodgers of their phones and other valuables, including an undisclosed amount of cash. The incident took place in Isuanaocha community. An eyewitness told The Nation on Monday that the hotel workers were taken unawares by the hoodlums. He said they ransacked the hotel looking for valuables and cash. “But after taking those things, they pounced on two female guests in the hotel and forcefully had carnal knowledge of them before they hurriedly leaving with their loot. Police spokesman Mohammed Haruna said the matter had not been reported.